problem.markdown:
>>Select three statements that apply to deep learning. <<

[x] A. Deep learning models leverage pattern recognition to automatically extract features from data distributions. {{selected: A. True, deep learning separates itself from classical machine learning by automating the feature selection process through pattern recognition.}}
[x] B. Deep learning involves building complex features from simpler features. {{selected: B. True, by using many hidden layers, deep learning models can combine simple features at lower layers to build up complex, highly abstract features at higher levels. }}
[ ] C. The compositionality principle states that the whole is made up of more than the parts. {{selected: C. Incorrect answer. The compositionality principle states that the whole is made of the parts, which is why complex features can be built from simpler features. It is an important assumption and must be made explicit. }}
[x] D. Good representations of data tend toward linear separability for classification tasks. {{selected: D. True, linearly separable representations of data allow classes to be distinguished with simpler functions, simplifying the optimization process.}}

{{ ((A B C D)) Please choose 3 options. }}

